f=Engineering/dana/operational/tool/dana-tool-requirements.md · p=What dana needs, what happens without each. dana's defining constraint: authors data changes never executes them (Rail 3). external tool call plan-locked (Rail sandboxed (Rail 2). · h2:Requirements=\| Need \| Tool / access \| Used by \| Without it \| · h2:Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Requirements=\| Schema/data READ access \| read scope on the store(s), per charter `read_access_scope` \| all skills \| Can't design against reality; escalate \| · h2:Requirements=\| Query-plan tool \| store's EXPLAIN-equivalent \| db-performance \| Timing + model reasoning only, labeled lower-fidelity \| · h2:Requirements=\| Scratch/restore environment \| to test down-scripts before up runs \| migration-discipline \| Production-shaped local copy, labeled debt; down-test never skipped \| · h2:Requirements=\| Production-scale sample data \| operator-supplied \| db-performance \| Best-available, labeled; no dev-scale conclusions \| · h2:Requirements=\| Append-only record access \| migration scripts \· schema docs (config paths) \| migration-discipline, data-modeling \| Can't record; loud degradation \| · h2:Requirements=\| HelixDB connector (if adopted) \| graph-vector store access \| datastore-selection, data-modeling \| Playbook is method-only until connected \| · h2:Explicit non-needs hard prohibition (by design)=**NO write/execute access any datastore ever, configurable (Rail 3).** dana authors migration scripts; OPERATOR runs them. department's central data-safety guarantee dana it's authored., **No application-code write access** dana designs data layer; raj implements access code., **No production execution anything** migrations handed operator; monitoring ops's. · n=asymmetry point: dana agent closest data therefore restricted changing it. Reads inform design; writes always human-executed., New store connectors enter stack-profile config store playbook, under locked plan. · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| Tool \| Source \| Purpose \| Always-on \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\|------\|--------\|---------\|-----------\| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Firecrawl MCP** \| [github.com/mcp/firecrawl](https://github.com/mcp/firecrawl/firecrawl-mcp-server) \| Structured web data extraction: scrape documentation sites → structured JSON for data pipelines, extract schemas/protocols from vendor docs, map competitor data models. \| ⚠️ On-demand — during data-modeling research phases \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Crawl4AI** \| [github.com/unclecode/crawl4ai](https://github.com/unclecode/crawl4ai) — Apache 2.0 \| RAG pipeline ingestion: crawl documentation → clean Markdown → vector DB. Async crawling for large documentation sites. BM25 noise filtering produces clean LLM input. \| ❌ No — Python library. Import in data pipeline scripts; runs as a tool dependency, not a continuous service \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=\| **Scrapling** \| [github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling](https://github.com/D4Vinci/Scrapling) — BSD 3-Clause \| JS-heavy site data extraction: when target sites require browser rendering (SPAs, dynamic content). Spider API for structured crawl workflows. Pause/resume for long-running extractions. \| ❌ No — escalate from Firecrawl only when JS rendering or stealth is needed \| · h2:MCP Marketplace Tools (added 2026-07-14)=See Engineering/MCP-MARKETPLACE.md setup tool selection decision guide.